Study Planner
Developers: Khushpreet Kaur and Prabhjot Kaur

Overview:

Study Planner is a React Native application designed to help users manage their study plans efficiently. The app allows users to add, edit, and delete tasks. It supports light and dark modes and ensures task data persistence using local storage.

Featues:

Task Management
Add tasks with name, description, date, and time.
Edit task details including status, name, and timing.
Mark tasks as "done" or "pending."
Delete tasks easily.
Dark and Light Mode
Toggle between light and dark themes.
User Profile
Add and edit user details including a profile picture.
Persistent storage for user details until edited.
Task List
View all tasks with their status.
Buttons to quickly edit or delete tasks.

Installation and Setup:
Prerequisites
Node.js (version 18+ recommended)
React Native CLI or Expo CLI
Android Studio (for Android emulation)
A text editor like VS Code

Steps to Install:
Clone the repository
Install dependencies
Run the app

Dependencies:
@react-native-community/datetimepicker: For selecting date and time.
@react-navigation/native: Navigation library for managing screens.
@react-navigation/stack: For stack-based navigation.
react-native-svg: To display custom SVG logos.
react-native-async-storage/async-storage: For local storage.
react-native-vector-icons: For icons used in navigation and UI.
expo-image-picker: To allow users to upload a profile picture.

File Structure:
App.js: Main entry point for the app.
src/screens/: Contains all screen components:
HomeScreen.js: Home screen with navigation options.
AddTaskScreen.js: Add new tasks.
TaskListScreen.js: View tasks with options to edit/delete.
TaskDetailScreen.js: Edit task details.
CalendarScreen.js: view tasks.
SettingsScreen.js: Profile and dark mode toggle.
src/components/: Reusable components (e.g., SVG logo).

How to Use:
Home Screen=>
Navigate to add tasks, view the calendar, or edit profile from the navigation buttons.
Add Task=>
Enter task details like name, description, date, and time.
Save the task to view it in the task list and calendar.
Task List=>
View all tasks and their statuses.
Mark tasks as done or pending.
Edit or delete tasks as needed.
Settings=>
Add or edit your profile.
Toggle between light and dark modes.

Future Improvements:
login option
Add integration with Google Calendar.
notifications
